      "## What is Cold-Centrifuged EVCO?",
      "Cold-centrifuged EVCO is produced using a unique method that involves extracting oil from fresh coconut milk without the use of heat or chemicals. This process retains the highest possible concentration of nutrients, including antioxidants and medium-chain fatty acids (MCFAs), making it one of the purest forms of coconut oil available.",
      "## Why Is It More Expensive?",
      "1. Advanced Extraction Process: unlike traditional methods that use heat or chemicals, cold-centrifugation gently separates the oil from coconut milk, preserving its natural goodness. This method is more complex, time-consuming, and requires specialized equipment, which increases the overall cost.",
      "2. Nutrient-Rich & Purity: since there's no exposure to heat, cold-centrifuged EVCO retains more antioxidants, natural aroma, and nutrients like MCFAs. The absence of chemical refining ensures you get the purest form of coconut oil — something you won't find in cheaper alternatives.",
      "3. Higher Coconut Requirement, Lower Yield: cold-centrifuged EVCO is made from fresh coconut milk rather than dried copra, which means more coconuts are required to produce the same amount of oil. The yield is lower, but the result is a higher quality product.",
